FBIS4-13491 "drnes077_n_94008" FBIS-NES-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 LEBANON Hizballah Deputies Criticize U.S. Envoy Hizballah Deputies Criticize U.S. Envoy NC2004182894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in Arabic 1730 GMT 20 Apr 94 NC2004182894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran Arabic BFN [Text] Hizballah representatives in the Lebanese Chamber of Deputies today accused U.S. Ambassador in Beirut Mark Hambley of interfering in Lebanon's internal affairs and insulting the sentiments of the Lebanese people. The deputies issued a statement pointing to the American ambassador's illogical movements and his threats to political trends in Lebanon. The statement says the American ambassador's moves violate diplomatic norms and aim to stand against the Lebanese Islamic and popular resistance against the Zionist occupier. The statement also stresses that recent military movements by the Zionist entity in south Lebanon are aimed at clearing that region of its inhabitants.
